title: The Religious Body - Catherine Aird (Unabridged)
description:
Unabridged and read by Robin Bailey. 5 hours 6 mins duration. 4 Cassettes. (32 kbps / 22 kHz Mono Fraunhofer CBR, jetAudio 6+).


[Inspector Sloan, Book 1, 1966]

Sister Anne has been thrown down the cellar stairs of the convent, and Inspector Sloan wonders who in God's name would want to murder a cloistered nun? Sloan's task is complicated by the unusual witnesses - 50-plus discreet, identically dressed nuns, each of whom has an assumed name and a past secular life!
